      "message": "If it\u0027s a field, you can\u0027t say:\n\nfunc (w *Image) Measure(t *theme.Theme) {\n    w.MeasuredSize \u003d etc\n}\n\nit would have to be w.Embed.MeasuredSize. Similarly for w.Wrapper or w.Rect, which is used in e.g. image.go, label.go, uniform.go, and any other widget...\n\nSimilarly, in node.go, you can\u0027t say:\n\nfunc (e *ContainerEmbed) Measure(t *theme.Theme) {\n  etc\n  for c :\u003d e.FirstChild; etc\n}\n\nit would have to be e.Embed.FirstChild, and similarly in flow.go, or any other container widget...\n\nSimilarly, you wouldn\u0027t be able to say:\n\nb :\u003d widget.NewButton(etc)\nb.LayoutData \u003d etc\n\nas it would have to be b.Embed.LayoutData...\n\nBasically, actually embedding the Embed, instead of just having a field, saves a lot of little \".Embed\"s everywhere.",
